title: Piano Sonata No. 16 in C Major, K. 545, I. Allegro

musicalLanguage.description: Mozart labeled this 'a little keyboard sonata for beginners,' but its simplicity is deceptive. Crystal-clear melodies and Alberti bass patterns make it a cornerstone of the Classical repertoire.
keyMoments: Opening theme: iconic ascending scale passage
Second theme: lyrical melody in G major
Recapitulation: themes return in C major
styleTips: Clean, even articulation â€” no pedal abuse
Alberti bass should be light and even
Phrasing should be elegant and vocal
